The paper deals with the problem of identifying probabilities from data sequences, which is a fundamental problem in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The technical tools used in the paper are the strong law of large numbers and the theory of Kolmogorov complexity, which are also relevant to the fields of data science (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of algorithms for prediction, which is a common theme in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
